commit.message:
CI mac/win: saner cache key involving ICU version and build plan

The cabal freeze file is not a good cache key as it contains e.g. the
hackage time stamp.  The build plan created by cabal build --dry-run
is more stable.

CI mac/win: do not add MSYS2/usr/bin to PATH (breaks caching)

See: https://github.com/actions/cache/issues/1073

We rather only add this path locally when we invoke pacman.
CI mac/win: cosmetic changes to satisfy shellcheck

Bump cabal-version to 1.18 for extra-doc-files

Since we only support GHC 7.10, which ships with Cabal-1.22, we can
bump the `cabal-version` without loss.  This allows to use the
`extra-doc-files` section for none-source files.

Remove `-fwarn-tabs` since it is implied by `-Wall`.

Do some cosmetic reformatting while we are at it.
Haskell CI: include GHC 9.6.1 alpha2

commit.message:
README: make PKG_CONFIG_PATH portable on macOS

Different macOS architectures have different homebrew install locations, it can be either `/usr/local`  or `/opt/homebrew`.  
The correct location is obtained via `brew --prefix`.
